This paper discusses the development of a three-dimensional (3D) channel model for mobile communication systems, which involves the use of multi-antenna techniques to exploit the elevation dimension. This topic is closely related to several areas of computer science, including information theory (cs.IT), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), multimedia (cs.MM), systems and control (cs.SY), and augmented reality (cs.AR). However, given the focus on wireless communication and signal processing, cs.IT and cs.NI are the most likely categories.
